    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Harlow</persName>,
                                    United States marshal, to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>, Secretary of State.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Marshal’s
                                        Office, Southern District of New York</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-11-10">
                        <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 10, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[121]</seg>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: From the activity which seems to
                                pervade Cuban circles, and from information gathered from the Junta
                                by my detectives, I am inclined to the opinion that measures are on
                                foot to get off an expedition. I have enjoined extra vigilance upon
                                all the detectives, and shall use every endeavor to stop any
                                expedition which may try to sail from this port. The *only source
                                from which I can get information relative to Cuban matters is from
                                the Spanish consul, and the superintendent and two detectives
                                connected with Pinkerton’s agency, whom I continue to employ the
                                same as my predecessor.</p>
                <p>I have only one revenue-cutter at my command—the Seward. If any
                                emergency arises, I shall do the very best that can be done with the
                                means at my command.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R. S. HARLOW,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Marshal.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton Fish</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
